Enum type for domain monitor activity.

Is not actually stored but just used as a counter signal to {@link #ACTIVE}.

description: User selected operation for a merge

fieldDocs.name: APPLY
fieldDocs.description:
The merge resolutions are to be applied without executing the final store operation. The user can inspect the merge
result in the original form context.

fieldDocs.name: CANCEL
fieldDocs.description: The store operation was canceled. The working set remains as-is.

fieldDocs.name: DISCARD
fieldDocs.description: The whole process is aborted and the current working set data is to be discarded.

fieldDocs.name: STORE
fieldDocs.description: Merge resolutions are applied to the working set and the final store operation is performed.

fieldDocs.description:
List of fields that are ignored in the merge, i.e. the last value always wins. This is useful for

fieldDocs.description:
List of field groups are that only merged together. A change in one field of a merge-group always creates a
conflict
for the whole group.
